ner output via `docker logs -f <containerID>`\n- Parse JSON-lines protocol messages (from cloche-agent):\n  - `step_started`: Record step in run + captures store\n  - `step_completed`: Record result + captures store\n  - `run_completed`: Set final run state\n  - `log`: Broadcast to live-stream subscribers\n\n**Post-exit cleanup** (lines 268-357):\n1. Wait for container exit: `docker wait <containerID>`\n2. Extract step outputs: `docker cp <containerID>:/workspace/.cloche/output/. <projectDir>/.cloche/<runID>/output`\n3. Capture full logs: `docker logs <containerID>` → `container.log`\n4. Index log files in log store (full.log, llm-*.log, script logs)\n5. Trigger evolution system if configured\n6. Fire orchestrator callback if configured\n7. Extract results to git branch via `docker.ExtractResults()`:\n   - Create temp dir with `docker cp <containerID>:/workspace/. <tmpDir>/`\n   - Create git worktree at `.gitworktrees/cloche/<runID>` from `BaseSHA`\n   - Copy temp contents to worktree (excluding .git)\n   - Create branch `cloche/<runID>` and commit\n8. Container retention policy:\n   - Failed runs: always keep for debugging\n   - Successful + `--keep-container`: keep\n   - Successful + no flag: `docker rm <containerID>`\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Domain Types**\n\n**Run** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`):\n- `ID`: Human-readable run ID (e.g., `develop-swift-oak`)\n- `WorkflowName`: Name of executed workflow\n- `State`: `pending|running|succeeded|failed|cancelled`\n- `ContainerID`: Docker container ID\n- `BaseSHA`: Git HEAD at run start\n- `ProjectDir`: Project root path\n- `StepExecutions`: Timeline of step start/complete events\n- `ActiveSteps`: Currently running steps\n\n**Workflow** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`):\n- `Steps`: Map of step name → step definition\n- `Wiring`: List of (from_step, result) → to_step edges\n- `Collects`: Multi-condition join logic\n- `EntryStep`: First step to execute\n- `Config`: Workflow-level settings (e.g., `container.image`, `container.agent_command`)\n\n**ContainerConfig** (`/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`):\n- `Image`: Docker image name\n- `WorkflowName`: Workflow name (maps to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`)\n- `ProjectDir`: Project root for `docker cp`\n- `RunID`: Passed to container as env var\n\n**ContainerRuntime Interface**:\n- `Start()`: Create and start container\n- `Stop()`, `Wait()`, `AttachOutput()`: Lifecycle\n- `CopyFrom()`, `Remove()`: Post-run extraction\n- `Inspect()`: Health check\n- Optional `EnsureImage()`: Image validation\n\n---\n\n### 6. **In-Container Execution** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/` + `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`)\n\n**Container startup:** Default command `cloche-agent .cloche/<workflow>.cloche`\n\n**Agent flow:**\n1. Parse `.cloche/<workflow>.cloche` DSL file\n2. Create unified log writer at `.cloche/output/`\n3. Create execution engine with step executor\n4. Walk workflow graph via `engine.Run()`:\n   - Launch entry step\n   - Poll result channel for step completions\n   - Process wiring to determine next steps\n   - Handle fanout (parallel branches) and collects (joins)\n   - Track state transitions\n5. Emit JSON-line protocol messages on stdout:\n   - `{\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"...\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}`\n   - `{\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"...\",\"result\":\"...\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}`\n   - `{\"type\":\"run_completed\",\"result\":\"succeeded|failed\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}`\n   - `{\"type\":\"log\",\"step_name\":\"...\",\"message\":\"...\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}`\n6. Exit with code 0 (success) or non-zero (failure)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Key Integration Points**\n\n**Image build trigger:**\n- Before every run if `EnsureImage()` is implemented (Docker does)\n- Not implemented in local runtime\n\n**Result extraction:**\n- Happens after container exit, inside `trackRun()`\n- Creates git branch with all workspace contents\n- Used for multi-step merge workflows via orchestrator\n\n**Evolution & Orchestration:**\n- Evolution trigger fires after run completes if configured\n- Orchestrator callback fires to enable CI/CD-like chaining\n- Both receive projectDir, runID, and final state\n\n**Log indexing:**\n- Full.log captures complete run transcript\n- llm-*.log and script logs indexed separately for filtering\n- Supports real-time streaming during run execution\n\n---\n\n### **Files to Understand the Complete System:**\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - RPC handlers and tracking logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go` - Image build & staleness detection\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` - Container lifecycle (create/start/copy)\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go` - Result extraction to git branches\n5. `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run state machine\n6. `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Workflow validation & execution graph\n7. `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` - ContainerRuntime interface & ImageEnsurer\n8. `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - In-container workflow execution\n9. `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` - Workflow graph execution (wiring, collects, fanout)\n10. `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` - JSON-line protocol messages"}],"totalDurationMs":98709,"totalTokens":58950,"totalToolUseCount":29,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":596,"cache_read_input_tokens":55817,"output_tokens":2537,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":596},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
